# Local static preview after FE changes

After making any change under `fe-artifacts/` (HTML, CSS, or JS), spin up a local
static server so the user can preview it — unless one is already running.

The web root is `fe-artifacts/` (pages use root-relative paths like `/assets`,
`/games`, `/tools`, `/profile.html`), so the server MUST be rooted there:

```bash
python3 -m http.server 8000 --bind 127.0.0.1
```

Run it from `fe-artifacts/` (or pass `--directory fe-artifacts`) as a background
process. Then give the user the URLs they can open, e.g.
`http://127.0.0.1:8000/`, `http://127.0.0.1:8000/games/`.

Notes:
- Before starting, check the terminals folder for an existing `http.server` on
  8000; reuse it instead of starting a duplicate.
- This is a static site with no build step — edits are picked up on refresh, so
  the server does not need restarting after further FE edits.
- Game data loads from Supabase at runtime; layout/styling still previews fine
  even if data calls fail locally.
